reviews.text: If you're not desperate for dessert, I would skip this place. The food wasn't bad, but it wasn't particularly memorable. The service was terrible. The two middle aged women that worked there looked like they hated their jobs and didn't treat patrons well at all. They were straight up rude. The menu is very typical of a local dessert shop and we had their shaved ice, which was OK but again not memorable. We wanted to add mixed fruit to our shaved ice but the rude staff said mixed fruit isn't an option. We would have had to add each variety of fruit separately. We thought that was ridiculous. They obviously had all of the fruit already. Pricing was average for such a dessert, around HK$40-50.
A very nice dessert specialist in Sai Wan Ho area which opens until mid-night. You can have all kind of desserts you can imagine

For anyone who can read this or care to even consider as an advise, i would say please bring your business to other nicer establishments around this neighbourhood. The desserts were ok but the guy who runs the shop has no patience for any questions and is always brusque and rude
